OL,3,CWere there 'missed opportunities' in
OL,4,Cthe lead up to the Nottingham attacks?
OL,6,FCalocane attended hospital, believing
OL,7,Fhe was having a heart attack and was
OL,8,Farrested after returning to his flat
OL,9,Fand causing damage to a door.JAn
OL,10,Fassessment under the mental health act
OL,11,Fwas carried out at a Nottingham
OL,12,Fcustody suite by psychiatric services,
OL,13,Fwho concluded that Calocane was
OL,14,Fpsychotic, but his risk to others was
OL,15,Flow.JHe was then referred to a crisis
OL,16,Fteam for a review at home, and he was
OL,17,Freleased without charge.JCalocane then
OL,18,Freturned to his apartment where he was
OL,19,Farrested for criminal damage for
OL,20,Fknocking down another door to a
OL,21,Fdifferent apartment.JHe was then
OL,22,Fadmitted to inpatient psychiatric
OL,23,Fservices at the Highbury Hospital.
