OL,3,CWere there 'missed opportunities' in
OL,4,Cthe lead up to the Nottingham attacks?
OL,6,FHe said: "I have personally reviewed
OL,7,Fthis matter and we should have done
OL,8,Fmore to arrest him. In my opinion it
OL,9,Fis highly unlikely that he would have
OL,10,Freceived a custodial sentence for the
OL,11,Falleged assault.
OL,13,F"Of course, an arrest may have
OL,14,Ftriggered a route back into mental
OL,15,Fhealth services, but as we have seen
OL,16,Ffrom his previous encounters with
OL,17,Fthose services, it seems unlikely that
OL,18,Fhe would have engaged in this process."
